product.name: Tie Belt Twill Coat
product.description: Calf length coat in twill. Features notch lapels and a wrap front with a concealed fastener. Wide, detachable tie belt at the waist. Raglan sleeves, diagonal welt front pockets and a single back vent. Lined.

materialDetails.name: Elastane
materialDetails.description: Elastane is a stretchy, synthetic fibre made from oil (a fossil resource). We have started using more sustainable alternatives, such as recycled elastane.

materialDetails.name: Polyester
materialDetails.description: Polyester is an artificial fibre made from fossil resources (crude oil). We are constantly striving to increase our use of recycled polyester — a more sustainable option made from waste such as plastic (PET) bottles. We are also engaging heavily in bio-based solutions and technologies that will enable textile-to-textile recycling, to further improve the sustainability of recycled polyester and save natural resources. In 2023 we will offer garments made of textile to textile recycled polyester.

materialDetails.name: Viscose
materialDetails.description: Viscose is a regenerated cellulose fibre commonly made from wood, but the raw material could also consist of other cellulosic materials. We are aiming to ensure that all wood used to make cellulosic fibres comes from sustainably managed forests or plantations. You can also find recycled viscose made from discarded cotton textiles in our assortment.
